# ============================================
# Capital City Windows Scheduler - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local (or .env) for local development.
# NEVER commit real secrets.
# ============================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# RAILWAY SETUP (Production)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# This project uses Railway with two services:
# - This Svelte app
# - Custom PocketBase (https://github.com/Remedine/pocketbase)
#
# Recommended: Use Railway **Shared Variables** (Project Settings)
# for values that must be identical across services:
#   - BREVO_API_KEY
#   - INTERNAL_SECRET   (must be the exact same value on both services)
#   - PUBLIC_POCKETBASE_URL
#   - PUBLIC_PB_URL
#
# INTERNAL_SECRET is a custom secret used to secure the internal
# PocketBase endpoints that generate email links (verification,
# password reset, email change). The Svelte server calls these
# endpoints, then sends the actual emails via Brevo (because
# SMTP is blocked on Railway free tier).
#
# PUBLIC_PB_URL  → Used by Svelte server routes to call PocketBase
#                  internal APIs (/api/internal/request-*)
# PUBLIC_POCKETBASE_URL → Used by the PocketBase JS SDK (client + server sync)
#
# PocketBase service also requires its own vars (see below).
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# === SVELTE APP (this repo) - Client-visible (PUBLIC_*) ===
# These are exposed to the browser.
PUBLIC_POCKETBASE_URL=https://pocketbase-production-e9a4.up.railway.app
PUBLIC_PB_URL=https://pocketbase-production-e9a4.up.railway.app

# === SVELTE APP - Server-only (never sent to browser) ===
INTERNAL_SECRET=HGd7AY@IZ*h61^EyQPHewRpw5u#n##bs        # Must EXACTLY match the value on the PocketBase service
BREVO_API_KEY=your-brevo-api-key-here                 # Brevo (Sendinblue) transactional email API key

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# POCKETBASE SERVICE (Remedine/pocketbase repo)
# These are set on the separate PocketBase Railway service.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Shared with Svelte:
INTERNAL_SECRET=your-long-random-secret-here          # Must match the Svelte service

# PocketBase-specific:
PB_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-32-byte-encryption-key-here    # Required by PocketBase for secure cookies/tokens
POCKETBASE_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
POCKETBASE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=your-strong-admin-password
POCKETBASE_PORT=8080
PORT=8080

# PB_PUBLIC_URL is used inside the custom main.go to build
# the full confirmation links sent in emails.
# It should point to the public URL of the PocketBase service.
PB_PUBLIC_URL=https://pocketbase-production-e9a4.up.railway.app

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# PUBLIC_POCKETBASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8090
# PUBLIC_PB_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8090
#
# INTERNAL_SECRET=dev-internal-secret-change-me
# BREVO_API_KEY=   # only needed if testing full email flows locally
#
# For local PocketBase (if running the custom binary):
# PB_ENCRYPTION_KEY=...
# POCKETBASE_ADMIN_EMAIL=...
# POCKETBASE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=...
# PORT=8090

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# NOTES
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# - All client-exposed variables must be prefixed with PUBLIC_.
# - Server-only secrets (INTERNAL_SECRET, BREVO_API_KEY) are read via
#   $env/static/private in SvelteKit server code.
# - After changing Railway variables, redeploy the affected service(s).
# - Generate strong random values for INTERNAL_SECRET and encryption keys
#   (e.g. 32+ characters, or use a password manager / openssl rand).
# - See the custom PocketBase main.go for how INTERNAL_SECRET and
#   PB_PUBLIC_URL are consumed on the backend side.
